<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-30T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-30T05:00:00-05:00" n="663" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d663">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3354: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-30T18:00:00+08:00">December 30, 1931—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 30—8:45 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>1156. The Military Attaché at Chinchow has just telephoned that the
                            Chinese troops are now withdrawing from that area to south of the Wall,
                            the movement to be complete within this week. Margetts has been
                            authorized by me to return at his discretion.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>